headline: Commercial heat pumps will benefit from tech developed for cold climate challenge, manufacturers say
summary: After successful residential trials, heat pump technologies for temperatures as low as minus 15 degrees Fahrenheit are being optimized for use in commercial buildings, executives at Carrier and Lennox said.
